Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; roughly chop into bite-size pieces. Halve, core, and slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Slice @mini cucumber{1} into ¼-inch-thick rounds.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Italian dressing{1.5%ounce}, half the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, and @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste. Add lettuce, bell pepper, cucumber, and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}; toss to coat.

> For 4 servings, use all the oregano, 2 TBSP olive oil, and ½ tsp sugar.

Tear @prosciutto{2%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Gently crush @croutons{1} in their bag.

> Refrigerate prosciutto until ready to use, so it's easier to tear!

Divide salad between bowls. Top with prosciutto and crushed croutons. Serve.